sequenceDiagram
    participant User as Data Scientist Browser
    participant Gateway as Data Science Gateway<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Proxy as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Notebook as Jupyter Notebook<br/>8888/TCP HTTP

    Note over User,Notebook: Flow 1: Authenticated Notebook Access

    User->>Gateway: GET /notebook/{ns}/{name}<br/>Auth: Bearer Token (OAuth)
    Gateway->>Proxy: Forward HTTPS Request<br/>TLS 1.2+ (service-ca cert)
    Proxy->>K8sAPI: SubjectAccessReview<br/>Verify "get" on Notebook CR<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>Proxy: Authorization Result

    alt User Authorized
        Proxy->>Notebook: Forward to localhost:8888<br/>HTTP (no encryption)
        Notebook-->>Proxy: Notebook UI Response
        Proxy-->>Gateway: HTTPS Response
        Gateway-->>User: Notebook Interface
    else User Denied
        Proxy-->>Gateway: 403 Forbidden
        Gateway-->>User: Access Denied
    end

    Note over User,Notebook: Flow 2: Unauthenticated Notebook Access

    User->>Gateway: GET /notebook/{ns}/{name}<br/>Auth: OpenShift OAuth
    Gateway->>Notebook: Direct to Service<br/>80/TCP HTTP
    Notebook-->>Gateway: Notebook UI Response
    Gateway-->>User: Notebook Interface

    Note over User,K8sAPI: Flow 3: Webhook Mutation

    participant APIServer as Kubernetes API Server
    participant Webhook as ODH Notebook Controller<br/>Webhook 8443/TCP HTTPS

    APIServer->>Webhook: POST /mutate-notebook-v1<br/>Notebook CREATE/UPDATE<br/>Auth: mTLS (client cert)
    Webhook->>Webhook: Check annotation:<br/>inject-auth: "true"

    alt Auth Injection Enabled
        Webhook->>APIServer: Mutated Notebook Spec<br/>(kube-rbac-proxy sidecar added)
    else No Auth
        Webhook->>APIServer: Original Notebook Spec
    end

    Note over User,K8sAPI: Flow 4: Controller Reconciliation

    participant Controller as ODH Notebook Controller
    participant Resources as K8s Resources<br/>(HTTPRoute, Service, etc.)

    Controller->>K8sAPI: Watch Notebook CRs<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: Notebook Event (create/update/delete)
    Controller->>Controller: Reconcile Loop:<br/>- Create HTTPRoute<br/>- Create ReferenceGrant<br/>- Create NetworkPolicy<br/>- Create RBAC objects
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create/Update Resources<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>Resources: Resources Applied

    Note over User,K8sAPI: Flow 5: Data Science Pipeline Integration

    participant DSPA as DSPA API<br/>8888/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+

    Controller->>K8sAPI: Watch DSPA CRs<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: DSPA Event
    Controller->>DSPA: Get Pipeline API Token<br/>Auth: Token from Secret
    DSPA-->>Controller: API Token
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Secret<br/>{notebook-name}-{dspa-name}-token<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: Secret Created
